caption: Good food and very reasonable prices

Best authentic Vietnamese food in town! I was quarantining and ordered the Vietnamese crepes and spring rolls — they reminded me from home. Not your typical chain Vietnamese restaurant, more like mom & dads cooking. The Vietnamese crepes and spring rolls both came with fresh veggies and sweet fish sauce. Well packaged. Makes me miss home! Highly recommend!

I have been in search for the perfect Phò for over thirty years; in parts of Africa, America, and Asia, and it has lead me to Phò Que Huong, right here in Hawaii. And I can honestly say without reservation that I have found what I believe to be a near perfect bowl of Phò I have ever tasted in my life!  Warning: This place opens at 0900hrs,  and the food, and staff are so good,  that if you arrive at 0935hrs. you may very well be too late to get a table!

A new favorite Vietnamese restaurant in Honolulu! The pho was well made...good ratio of noodles to meat, and the broth was tasty. Spring rolls we're good...nothing to complain about. The bahn mi bbq chicken sandwich was excellent... delicious fillings and perfectly crunchy bread that doesn't cut up the inside of your mouth. Access to the restaurant is on the 2nd floor of the Chinatown municipal parking lot, or accessible from the street. Service was quick and friendly. We will definitely be back.

This newly opened Vietnamese restaurant in the heart of Chinatown has an extensive menu with familiar items such as banh mi sandwiches and pho dishes ... but they also have more exotic offerings such as the Goat Hot Pot, (see photos). This dish ($45) can easily feed 4 people. The goat meat is a little tough but not gamey - something to try on a chilly day when you’re feeling adventurous!  They also serve traditional Vietnamese iced coffee - once it’s brewed you pour it into a glass with ice.  Parking is available at nearby municipal garages - both underground and open air. Many are leery about going into Chinatown because of the many homeless folks but I’ve never felt unsafe during the day - haven’t been there at night!
